title: For Sale:  1997 Rokon Trail-Breaker
postcontent: If you're not familiar with these 2X2 bikes...they are cool as hell. Can carry up to 1000 pounds and tow up to 3000 pounds. Drum wheels are hollow, allowing for extra fuel and/or water. The bike will also float...no more getting a buddy to winch your quad off the bottom of the lake. 49cc Chrysler Power-Bee motor w/Tillitsen carb (engine will run on it's side or even upside down). Three-speed, plunger type transmission. Top speed is maybe 35mph, but this thing will climb the side of your neighbor's house. Tackles trails, hills, and other terrain that a quad wouldn't dream of. Great for hunters, trappers, or those wishing to escape the zombie apocalypse. Just to prove how bad-ass they are...Stallone used one to take out a helicopter in Expendibles 2! Seriously though...I have two of them and they are a lot of fun. I can't justify needing both, as my wife and kids are scared of them. But I will be keeping one...forever. Check out the inter-web, you'll find a lot of info, accessories, and attachments for these bikes.

The P-01 is a compact, alloy-framed decocker model with light rail.

SKU: 91199.
Categories: 75 Compact 
Product Description

The P-01 9mm (accompanied by the P-06 in .40 S&W) was designed for LE and Military duty, but its compact size and the reduced weight due to its forged alloy frame made it ideal for discrete carry as well. Equipped with a decocker, the P-01 provides convenience for those who prefer hammer-down carry. The P-01 was the first CZ model to benefit from updated manufacturing technology at CZ’s Uhersky Brod factory. The components of the P-01/P-06 are completely interchangable with every other P-01/P-06, with no individual fitting required. This required some very careful re-design so that the reliability and accuracy were not impaired. Since the time of its introduction (designed in 2001, NATO-approved in 2003) the production upgrades have been rolled out to most of the CZ 75 family and several new rifle models as well. The 1913 accessory rail easily accepts any of the industry-standard lights and lasers to assist low-light use. After 3 years of some of the most aggressive small arms testing ever, the CZ P-01 won the honor of replacing the CZ 75s previously used by the Czech National Police. Reliability:  The U.S. Army “Mean Rounds Between Failure” (MRBF) requirement is 495 rounds for 9mm pistols. During testing of the CZ P-01, the average number of stoppages was only 7 per 15,000 rounds fired. This is a .05% failure rate or an MRBF of 2142! For many years, the P-01 carried an NSN engraved on its frame, making it the first NATO-spec pistol ever available to the public. Recently, the factory decided to upgrade the slide stop spring which in turn means the current models may not carry the NSN

location: Santa Fe, NM, New Mexico, United States
postcontent:
Here is a never-issued Yugo SKS as in the title. It has a couple of excellent upgrades for reliability. (1) Murray's spring loaded firing pin. New style, won't break. (2) Wolff mainspring - again for reliability and certain ignition.

Yugo SKS's are not even in the same league as a Chinese SKS, and I like them better than the original Russian ones too. The stocks fit Americans and are longer than either Russian or Chinese stocks. They aren't seemingly made for midgets. The finish is super on them - especially the unissued ones like this.

This is a Model 59/66 A-1. So it is the highest evolved SKS. The integral grenade launcher also acts as a flash suppressor. the pop-up front and rear night sights are present. It has its original folding bayonet. the rifle is all matching including the original teak stock, and the magazine and trigger guard. The cleaning kit is present in the butt.

My son and I regularly shoot this one at (and HIT) an 18 inch steel plate at 500 yards with it. It is extremely accurate for an SKS. Not a toy. It is also a collectible rifle as well as a practical one. Ammunition for these is something on the order of $5.89 for a box of 20 at Walmart or Sportmen's Warehouse. 

The rifle's condition is virtually mint, and there are no dents, dings, or scratches on it. 

Price is $400, or I might take an interesting trade or partial trade on it. You will like this SKS. 

Contact me through Armslist and we'll get together for you to see it in Santa Fe. I will be willing to ship to your FFL as well for an additional $25 on receipt of payment should that be better for you.

title: For Sale/Trade:  CZ P-01
postcontent:
I'm converting to .40 S&W ammo so I'm considering trading my all time favorite gun the CZ P-01. Would love to trade for a CZ P-06, HK USP Compact, possibly a springfield xdm in OD green .40. I also have approximately 500 rounds of ammo to go with in trade for .40 ammo. 

The P-01 is a compact, alloy-framed decocker model with light rail.

SKU: 91199.
Categories: 75 Compact 
Product Description

The P-01 9mm (accompanied by the P-06 in .40 S&W) was designed for LE and Military duty, but its compact size and the reduced weight due to its forged alloy frame made it ideal for discrete carry as well. Equipped with a decocker, the P-01 provides convenience for those who prefer hammer-down carry. The P-01 was the first CZ model to benefit from updated manufacturing technology at CZ’s Uhersky Brod factory. The components of the P-01/P-06 are completely interchangable with every other P-01/P-06, with no individual fitting required. This required some very careful re-design so that the reliability and accuracy were not impaired. Since the time of its introduction (designed in 2001, NATO-approved in 2003) the production upgrades have been rolled out to most of the CZ 75 family and several new rifle models as well. The 1913 accessory rail easily accepts any of the industry-standard lights and lasers to assist low-light use. After 3 years of some of the most aggressive small arms testing ever, the CZ P-01 won the honor of replacing the CZ 75s previously used by the Czech National Police. Reliability:  The U.S. Army “Mean Rounds Between Failure” (MRBF) requirement is 495 rounds for 9mm pistols. During testing of the CZ P-01, the average number of stoppages was only 7 per 15,000 rounds fired. This is a .05% failure rate or an MRBF of 2142! For many years, the P-01 carried an NSN engraved on its frame, making it the first NATO-spec pistol ever available to the public.

Up for sale is a beretta 92fs . I've put close to 10,000 rounds through it and noticed a slight bulge in the barrel . I've never had a squib and have personally put most of the rounds through the gun . I  contacted beretta and they said it was common with barrels towards the end of their life . Not sure how I did it with 10,000 rounds, i think theyre rated for over 30,000 rounds and I haven't even put many hp through it . But I don't shoot it anymore so I've factored a new barrel and new recoil
Spring into the asking price cash only and not willing to travel  .Also , the rifling looks perfect . Typically you'll see a dark spot where the bulge is located but the rifling looks brand new which leads me to think there was some sort of defect in the barrel to cause it to start to fail
Prematurely . I had a gunsmith friend of mine look it over and shoot it . He said it wasn't an issue . The only reason I even mention the barrel is so you know exactly what your getting and so there's no surprises once the deals been made . title: For Sale:  NEED TO SELL: Custom 1911 .45ACP
postcontent:
I am selling my custom Remington R1 1911 that's been extensively worked on and upgraded with Wilson Combat parts.  The only reason I'm doing this right now is to pay for repairs on a vehicle that was in an accident mid last week, so I'm not going to be able to entertain any trade requests or drop the price as I'm already losing almost $200 to sell it quickly.  First things first, here are the specs on the 1911 from the factory:

Caliber: .45 Auto
Magazine: 7+1
Barrel: Stainless
Twist: 1-16 LH
Overall Length: 8.5"
Overall Height: 5.5"
Trigger Pull: 3.5 - 5 lbs.
Finish: Satin Black Oxide
Grips: Double Diamond Walnut
Avg. Wt. (oz.): 38.5
MSRP: $729.00

With that said and done I'll tell you that a lot of time and energy has gone in to this weapon since I received it a month ago in trade, including a trigger job.  The feed ramp has been polished, the barrel has been polished and throated.  The base of the firing pin stop has been polished.  The trigger bow has been polished and the trigger channel deburred.  The sear and disconnector have been deburred and polished on the surfaces that required it.  The sear spring has been polished and adjusted slightly.

With all the smithing out of the way on to the Wilson Combat parts that were fitted and installed: hammer, wide competition thumb safety, competition match trigger, beavertail.  It comes with Pearce Grip rubber side panel grips.  This firearm also has a match grade barrel installed in it.  All in all what I have in to this weapon is nearly $950 when all things are said and done, not including what you'd normally spend on a gunsmith to do a trigger job and polish all the internals. which can easily be $75-150 depending on who you use.  The only flaw is a small scratch next to the magazine release from the previous owner, but I had eventually planned to cerakote the frame in FDE and toss desert digital grips on it, so it didn't bother me.  It has just about 200rds through it and it can run everything I put in to it.  It's run Federal aluminum, TulAmmo steel, Winchester white box, and Remington gold saber without a single hiccup.  This weapon is a super reliable tack driver now and would be great for home defense or EDC.  I'm former law enforcement and do some firearm instruction and I would trust the lives of my family to it, it's that reliable.

I'm asking $750 out the door for this weapon and it will come with all the original stock parts, hard plastic Remington case, and two 7rd magazines.  I will also require a valid FL driver's license and a bill of sale to be signed to protect both parties.  If you have any questions or would like to see more pictures, please contact me.  If you're going to offer less than I'm asking or to trade, please don't waste either of our time, this is a heck of a deal and it makes me sick to sell my project gun, but need outweighs toys.

Have a good one!
